\series bold
Abstract
\series default
: This is a
\series bold
 pencil and paper proof
\series default
 of the four color problem.
 This problem, stated in terms of graph theory, that every loopless planar
 graph admits a vertex coloring with at most four different colors, was
 proved back in 1976 by Appel and Haken, using a computer.
 Many people are still trying to solve it the old way and I am one of them.
 This paper shows two important results: 
\series bold
1)
\series default
 Only maps with faces that have five edges or more can be considered to
 find a proof of the theorem; 
\series bold
2)
\series default
 All maps can be deformed into circular maps or represented as rectangular
 maps, which are more manageable forms of maps
\end_layout

