\begin_layout Standard
All regular maps can be transformed into circular maps! Here is the proof:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

It is straightforward to consider a map as a jigsaw puzzle, if we imagine
 that the faces that compose the map are the pieces of the puzzle itself.
 This way to consider maps has the important advantage to imagine the process
 of construction as made of consecutive steps (piece after piece construction),
 as anyone would do with a real jigsaw puzzle.
 This method of construction is useful to show how maps can be transformed
 (or visualized) in other ways, such as 
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

